OL,3,C'Never take peace for granted':
OL,4,CSurvivor of Bosnian War visits Jersey
OL,6,FSmajo was just seven years old when
OL,7,Fthe war broke out in Bosnia - his
OL,8,Ffather and several male relatives
OL,9,Fended up being tortured in
OL,10,Fconcentration camps, as Muslims became
OL,11,Fthe targets of genocide.
OL,13,FHe says: "The Bosnian Genocide
OL,14,Fhappened in the heart of Europe just
OL,15,F50 years on from the Holocaust.
OL,17,F"The lesson from Bosnia is that we
OL,18,Fmust never be complacent or take peace
OL,19,Ffor granted because it exposed how
OL,20,Fvulnerable and fragile society can be.
